		<p>Semantic arguments aside.  I have a real need for a license that is not covered by &#8220;Free&#8221; or &#8220;Common&#8221; or &#8220;CopyRight or Left&#8221;</p>
<p>So I&#8217;ve been working 3 years and investing 6 figures of my own money solving some important problems.  I know my (software) solution is not the end game and I want people to build on it &#8211; freely but not for free:  If someone makes money off my work product I would like a piece, but they shouldn&#8217;t have to pay me or even get my permission up front.  If someone wants to use my product for their own benefit, then they can give me a monetary &#8220;thank you&#8221; or not.</p>
