		<p>You raise good points, Nina, but you have to go deeper to find the root of these issues. What&#8217;s at stake here is who benefits from the production. It must be producers and consumers, with exploiters excluded. This is the whole point, which nor copyright nor this &#8220;copyleft&#8221; manages to address. </p>
<p>Dmytri Kleiner makes this point very clear in his &#8220;Contribution to The Critique of Free Culture&#8221;, a chapter in the Telekommunist Manifesto (<a href="http://docs.telekommunisten.org/The+Telekommunist+Manifesto" rel="nofollow">http://docs.telekommunisten.org/The+Telekommunist+Manifesto</a>, hardcopies and PDF also available at <a href="http://www.telekommunisten.net/the-telekommunist-manifesto" rel="nofollow">http://www.telekommunisten.net/the-telekommunist-manifesto</a>).</p>
